params.claimableTime: Token claimable time if auction success.
params.funder: The address that funds the token for BatchAuction.
params.maximumCommitmentAmount: Maximum amount collected at which the auction will be successful.
params.minimumCommitmentAmount: Minimum amount collected at which the auction will be successful.
params.token: Address of the token being sold.
params.totalTokens: The total number of tokens to sell in auction.
params.wallet_: Address where collected funds will be forwarded to.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

pauseAuction().details: Admin can pause auction during auction.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner.     * NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

resumeAuction(uint256).details: Admin can resume auction and can extend end time

params.wallet_: Auction wallet is where funds will be sent.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
